ValueMeaning.preferredName: Tanner Pubic Hair Development Stage 1, Female
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Vellus hair develops over the pubes in a manner not greater than that over the anterior wall. There is no sexual hair.

Concepts.longName: Tanner Pubic Hair Development Stage 1, Female
Concepts.definition: Vellus hair develops over the pubes in a manner not greater than that over the anterior wall. There is no sexual hair.

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Tanner Pubic Hair Development Stage 2, Female
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Sparse, long, pigmented, downy hair, which is straight or only slightly curled, appears. These hairs are seen mainly along the labia. This stage is difficult to quantitate on black and white photographs, particularly when pictures are of fair-haired subjects.

Concepts.longName: Tanner Pubic Hair Development Stage 2, Female
Concepts.definition: Sparse, long, pigmented, downy hair, which is straight or only slightly curled, appears. These hairs are seen mainly along the labia. This stage is difficult to quantitate on black and white photographs, particularly when pictures are of fair-haired subjects.

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Tanner Pubic Hair Development Stage 3, Female
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Considerably darker, coarser, and curlier sexual hair appears. The hair has now spread sparsely over the junction of the pubes.

Concepts.longName: Tanner Pubic Hair Development Stage 3, Female
Concepts.definition: Considerably darker, coarser, and curlier sexual hair appears. The hair has now spread sparsely over the junction of the pubes.

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Tanner Pubic Hair Development Stage 4, Female
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The hair distribution is adult in type but decreased in total quantity. There is no spread to the medial surface of the thighs.

Concepts.longName: Tanner Pubic Hair Development Stage 4, Female
Concepts.definition: The hair distribution is adult in type but decreased in total quantity. There is no spread to the medial surface of the thighs.

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Tanner Pubic Hair Development Stage 5, Female
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Hair is adult in quantity and type and appears to have an inverse triangle of the classically feminine type. There is spread to the medial surface of the thighs but not above the base of the inverse triangle.

Concepts.longName: Tanner Pubic Hair Development Stage 5, Female
Concepts.definition: Hair is adult in quantity and type and appears to have an inverse triangle of the classically feminine type. There is spread to the medial surface of the thighs but not above the base of the inverse triangle.

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Tanner Pubic Hair Development Stage 1, Male
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Vellus hair appears over the pubes with a degree of development similar to that over the abdominal wall. There is no androgen-sensitive pubic hair.

Concepts.longName: Tanner Pubic Hair Development Stage 1, Male
Concepts.definition: Vellus hair appears over the pubes with a degree of development similar to that over the abdominal wall. There is no androgen-sensitive pubic hair.

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Tanner Pubic Hair Development Stage 2, Male
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: There is sparse development of long pigmented downy hair, which is only slightly curled or straight. The hair is seen chiefly at the base of penis. This stage may be difficult to evaluate on a photograph, especially if the subject has fair hair.

Concepts.longName: Tanner Pubic Hair Development Stage 2, Male
Concepts.definition: There is sparse development of long pigmented downy hair, which is only slightly curled or straight. The hair is seen chiefly at the base of penis. This stage may be difficult to evaluate on a photograph, especially if the subject has fair hair.

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Tanner Pubic Hair Development Stage 3, Male
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The pubic hair is considerably darker, coarser, and curlier. The distribution is now spread over the junction of the pubes, and at this point that hair may be recognized easily on black and white photographs.

Concepts.longName: Tanner Pubic Hair Development Stage 3, Male
Concepts.definition: The pubic hair is considerably darker, coarser, and curlier. The distribution is now spread over the junction of the pubes, and at this point that hair may be recognized easily on black and white photographs.

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Tanner Pubic Hair Development Stage 4, Male
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The hair distribution is now adult in type but still is considerably less that seen in adults. There is no spread to the medial surface of the thighs.

Concepts.longName: Tanner Pubic Hair Development Stage 4, Male
Concepts.definition: The hair distribution is now adult in type but still is considerably less that seen in adults. There is no spread to the medial surface of the thighs.

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Tanner Pubic Hair Development Stage 5, Male
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Hair distribution is adult in quantity and type and is described in the inverse triangle. There can be spread to the medial surface of the thighs.

Concepts.longName: Tanner Pubic Hair Development Stage 5, Male
Concepts.definition: Hair distribution is adult in quantity and type and is described in the inverse triangle. There can be spread to the medial surface of the thighs.
